title: Google\Cloud\Deploy\V1\PrivatePool
name: PrivatePool
description:
Execution using a private Cloud Build pool.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.deploy.v1.PrivatePool

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.worker_pool
params.description: Required. Resource name of the Cloud Build worker pool to use. The format is projects/{project}/locations/{location}/workerPools/{pool}.

params.name: data.service_account
params.description: Optional. Google service account to use for execution. If unspecified, the project execution service account (-compute@developer.gserviceaccount.com) will be used.

params.name: data.artifact_storage
params.description: Optional. Cloud Storage location where execution outputs should be stored. This can either be a bucket ("gs://my-bucket") or a path within a bucket ("gs://my-bucket/my-dir"). If unspecified, a default bucket located in the same region will be used.
